# Badge Component Guide

Badges are compact, visually distinct labels used to highlight status, categorize content, or display short pieces of information. This guide provides comprehensive instructions for implementing badges in your application.

## Basic Badge Structure

The base badge component follows a consistent structure with specific class naming conventions:

```html
<span class="badge">
    <span class="badge-text">Label</span>
</span>
```

By default, badges have the following styling:
- Blue background (`var(--secondary-blue-500-base)`)
- White text (`var(--neutral-white)`)
- Large border radius (`var(--radius-large)`)
- Uppercase text with letter spacing
- Fixed height of 20px (`var(--space-5)`)
- Horizontal padding of 8px (`var(--space-2)`)

## Badge Text Element

The badge text element must always be wrapped in a `<span>` with the class `badge-text`:

```html
<span class="badge-text">Label</span>
```

This approach ensures:
- Proper text styling (uppercase, letter spacing)
- Consistent vertical alignment
- Text remains contained within the badge boundaries

