## Badges with Icons

To include an icon within a badge, use the `badge-with-icon` class and icon container:

```html
<span class="badge badge-with-icon">
    <div class="icon-container">
        <i class="fa-solid fa-info-circle"></i>
    </div>
    <span class="badge-text">Info</span>
</span>
```

For success badges with icons:

```html
<span class="badge badge-success badge-with-icon">
    <div class="icon-container">
        <i class="fa-solid fa-check-circle"></i>
    </div>
    <span class="badge-text">Success</span>
</span>
```

The `badge-with-icon` class:
- Adds proper spacing (`gap: var(--space-1)`) between icon and text
- Ensures proper alignment of icon and text
- Maintains consistent sizing

## Inline Badge Usage

When using badges within text content, add the `badge-inline` class for proper spacing:

```html
<p class="body-text">
    This feature is currently in development 
    <span class="badge badge-inline">
        <span class="badge-text">Beta</span>
    </span>
</p>
```

The `badge-inline` class adds a left margin (`var(--space-2)`) to create proper spacing from the preceding text.

## Usage in Overview Cards

Badges can be used in overview cards to indicate metrics trends:

```html
<div class="overview-card__subtitle">
    <span class="badge badge-success">
        <span class="badge-text">+12%</span>
    </span>
    <span style="margin-left: var(--space-1);">since last month</span>
</div>
```

For negative trends, use the error badge:

```html
<div class="overview-card__subtitle">
    <span class="badge badge-error">
        <span class="badge-text">-2.3%</span>
    </span>
    <span style="margin-left: var(--space-1);">since last week</span>
</div>
```

